title: One Nation is a ‘different product on the shelf’: Barnaby Joyce
description: One Nation MP Barnaby Joyce says his party is a “new product on the shelf” of Australian politics.  “It is a political marketplace,” Mr Joyce said.  “There is a different product on the shelf and they are buying it, it is called One Nation.”

title: Interest rate hike is ‘all but guaranteed’
description: Sky News host Danica De Giorgio says an interest rate hike is “all but guaranteed” as inflation rose to 3.8 per cent in the last 12 months to December.  “Stronger than expected,” Ms De Giorgio said.  “While the Consumer Price Index also rose to 3.4 per cent in November.”

title: ‘Excessive government spending’: Interest rate hike causes analysed
description: Macrobusiness Chief Economist Leith Van Onselen says inflation is so high due to “excessive government spending”.  “Australia’s inflation is so high … because public demand, which is basically government spending is at a near-record high share of GDP,” Mr Van Onselen said.  “It is actually the highest in Australia’s history outside of the pandemic.”

title: Albanese should ‘fire’ Race Discrimination Commissioner over Australia Day comments
description: Sky News host James Macpherson says if Prime Minister Anthony Albanese is serious about social cohesion, then he should fire his Race Discrimination Commissioner Giridharan Sivaraman.  “If uniting the country is the goal, well it is hard to see how paying a public servant $400,000 a year to preach division is part of the plan,” Mr Macpherson says.  “Have a listen to our taxpayer-funded race commissioner holding court on our taxpayer-funded broadcaster explaining to taxpayers that they are in fact squatters.”

title: Public servants take 50 per cent more ‘sickies’ than private workers
description: Sky News host James Macpherson says public servants are taking 50 per cent more “sickies” than workers in the private sector according to a new report.  “A report tabled in the New South Wales parliament last week revealed public servants are taking almost 50 per cent more sickies than workers in the private sector,” Mr Macpherson said.  “The figures invite cynicism.”

title: ‘Damaging revelations for the Royal Family’: Andrew in new ‘shocking’ Epstein files photos
description: GB News host Emily Carver reacts to “shocking” new photos of Andrew Mountbatten-Windsor, which were released by the US Department of Justice in the latest batch of Jeffrey Epstein files.  “It’s absolutely shocking, yet another string of damaging revelations for the Royal Family from these Epstein files,” Ms Carver told Sky News host Danica De Giorgio.  “What on Earth was a member of our Royal Family doing posing for ridiculous photos with what looks like a young woman playing dead on the floor?   “None of this seems to bother Andrew himself, the arrogant man that we all know; he was seen out riding yesterday, photographed laughing and smiling as if nothing was going on.”

title: ‘Absolutely laughable’: Keir Starmer criticised for seeking China’s help on migrant crisis
description: GB News host Emily Carver criticises UK Prime Minister Keir Starmer for seeking China’s assistance to prevent migrants from crossing the Channel.  “You couldn’t make it up, this man has absolutely no idea what he’s doing, I’m talking about the Prime Minister, of course,” Ms Carver told Sky News host Danica De Giorgio.  “So rather than police our own borders, which we’ve been begging him to do … he’s actually asking the Chinese, a hostile state, who spy on us incessantly, to help him out a bit.  “They must be absolutely laughing at us at this point … could this be more of a gimmick if he tried?  “Why on Earth are we trusting China to help us out on this one?”

title: Coalition must do ‘a lot better’ to cut through Labor’s spin
description: Nationals MP Michael McCormack says the Liberal and National Parties are not in a shambles, but they need to do a “lot better”.  “We’ve got a housing crisis, we’ve got people paying $21,000 a year more on their mortgage repayments than they were under the former Coalition,” Mr McCormack said.  “We’ve got rents up 22 per cent, power bills up 40 per cent and food up 16 per cent and Anthony Albanese’s making jokes.”

title: Albanese ‘so confident’ as Coalition infighting spills to leadership row
description: Sky News host Paul Murray analyses the fight for the future of the Coalition between the Liberal and Nationals.  “The leadership of both the Liberal and National Party and its members has given, essentially, a free kick to the prime minister,” Mr Murray said.  “This is kind of like the ‘hokey pokey’, you put your MPs you put your shadow ministers out.”

title: ‘We know the truth’: Iranian regime attempts to deny and hide ‘merciless’ crackdown
description: Human rights lawyer Arsen Ostrovsky analyses the Iranian regime and their attempt to “hide the truth” behind its “merciless” protest crackdown.  “The death toll could be significantly higher … as much as this Iranian regime may try and hide the truth,” Mr Ostrovsky said.  “We know the truth.”

title: Disgraced Andrew has ‘nothing to gain’ from US Congress testimony
description: Spiked Online Editor Tom Slater questions whether disgraced former Prince Andrew would testify before the US Congress.  “I don't think there is anything to gain for him or the Royal Family in him going to address the US Congress,” Mr Slater told Sky News host James Macpherson.  “I just don’t see how this is going to end in anything other than Andrew continuing to kind of slink to the edges of public life and try to avoid this story and ride it out.  “I would be amazed even if Prince Andrew was frankly dumb enough to reopen this and try to clear his name in front of the US Congressmen and women.”

title: ‘More damning details’: New images in Epstein files reignite focus on Andrew
description: Spiked Online Editor Tom Slater discusses new photos of Andrew Mountbatten-Windsor, which the US Department of Justice released in the latest batch of Jeffrey Epstein files.  “I dare say he would be sweating now, there’s imagery here, there’s that image that has now gone across the world of him appearing to crouch over a young woman,” Mr Slater told Sky News host James Macpherson.  “There’s also much more damning details, I think, about just how close the relationship between the former prince and the disgraced pedophile financer were, even after he claimed to have broken up the relationship.”

title: One Nation hits ‘highest’ poll numbers ‘ever’
description: Sky News host Paul Murray highlights how One Nation is “topping the charts” in new polling results placing Pauline Hanson’s party above the Coalition.  “They have just hit their highest number ever,” Mr Murray said.  “In any poll, and it is a very serious poll for them to be topping the charts at.”

title: New photos of Andrew described as ‘extraordinarily damaging’
description: TalkTV host Mark Dolan says new photos of disgraced former prince Andrew are “extraordinarily damaging” to the Royal Family.   “Just when you thought things couldn’t get worse for Andrew,” Mr Dolan told Sky News host Paul Murray.  “Obviously, you’ve got the email exchange between him and Jeffrey Epstein.  “That’s one thing, but this new photo is extraordinarily damaging to the Royal Family, and it means that Andrew’s brand, if it wasn’t already damaged, it’s over now.”

title: ‘Here come the hit jobs’: Media takes swipe at One Nation
description: On tonight’s episode of Paul Murray Live, Sky News host Paul Murray discusses One Nation’s polling, Sussan Ley’s leadership spill, US politics and more.
